# CUBE-4

**CUBE-4** is a 3D, two-player abstract strategy game played on a 4Ã—4Ã—4 cube.  
Players take turns placing pieces anywhere in the cube, aiming to be the first to align **four pieces in a straight line** â€” in any direction.

This is a browser-based implementation using **Three.js**.

---

## ðŸŽ¯ Game Rules

- The board is a **4Ã—4Ã—4 cube** (64 positions)
- Two players: **Red** and **Blue**
- Players alternate turns
- On your turn, place a piece on **any empty position** (no gravity)
- A win is achieved by placing **four pieces in a straight line**, including:
  - Rows, columns, or verticals
  - Diagonals on a face
  - Diagonals through the cube (3D diagonals)

Winning pieces are highlighted in yellow.

---

## ðŸ•¹ Controls

- **Rotate board:** click and drag
- **Zoom:** mouse wheel / trackpad
- **Place piece:** hover over a marker and click
- **Undo:** revert one move at a time
- **Reset:** start a new game
- **?**: show game instructions

The cube outline colour indicates the current playerâ€™s turn.

---

## ðŸ§  Visual Aids

- Hovering over a position highlights:
  - The current playerâ€™s colour
  - The entire level (layer) being targeted
- Other levels fade back to improve clarity
- Accidental placements while rotating are prevented

